snippet.textDisplay:
For those crticizing Lia for being a "lazy" dancer, please remember that she's not the best dancer in the group.

People, or should I say mostly K-netz, have been pointing out that in the first part of the choreo, she doesn't move her shoulders like the other members do. I am not a professional dancer or at any point studied dance but I can tell that she can't quite do the move. I've been observing idols "shortcutting" their moves but it is not a sign of being "lazy". It just shows a little bit of an underdeveloped technique than the others who are good at it. So it might cause her to not be able to do the move. People also add that her facial expressions are "inconsistent", which I would not prove wrong. She does tend to deplete in facials for sometime but I think it is because it is really hard to dance and be able to create expressions at the same time.

All in all, I think that Lia is just not as good as the other members. Not saying that she is a bad dancer. She certainly is a good idol dancer; she can even dance better than those haters. Just remember that idols are not perfect human beings who can always conform to what you want. They also have flaws and they always try to cover it by hard work. So to those who say tha Lia is being "lazy", know your facts firsts before you come at us. :))))))

snippet.textDisplay: I noticed how "different" Lia moves that it stands out and recently found out that she's been accused of being a lazy dancer. Here's what I think as an amateur dancer: she is not being lazy. It's true that she is not executing some certain parts of the choreography completely. Specifically the steps that require wide, fast movements. Control is very important. I've observed that she rather throws her movements instead of holding it, if you know what I mean. When you simply throw your movement, it takes you a fraction of a second longer to take control of your body thus making it hard for you to change steps quickly and move in timing. Because of that, you are forced to do a "shortcut" to keep up with the choreography, preventing you from fully executing the move. This can be fixed by detecting and correcting it early, so as not to get used to it, and continuous practice. Lia will learn it soon, I believe so. Again, just my thoughts.
